1
00:01:33,226 --> 00:01:34,294
Have you become

2
00:01:34,327 --> 00:01:35,495
a knife in Director Sheng's hand,

3
00:01:37,831 --> 00:01:39,265
with the blade pointed straight at me?

4
00:01:47,974 --> 00:01:49,142
If I were a knife,

5
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:52,879
I'd only be one that saves lives.

6
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:55,782
I wouldn't hurt anyone.

7
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:07,093
Director Zhou,

8
00:02:09,562 --> 00:02:10,530
I'm just a doctor.

9
00:02:11,564 --> 00:02:12,765
I'm only responsible for operating.

10
00:02:14,534 --> 00:02:16,603
I'm not interested in your political infighting.

11
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:30,850
Lin Yi.

12
00:02:56,409 --> 00:02:57,277
From now on,

13
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:00,146
I won't keep yielding to you.

14
00:03:51,164 --> 00:03:51,598
Eryi.

15
00:03:52,031 --> 00:03:52,565
Brother Yi.

16
00:04:28,134 --> 00:04:28,935
You want to add more?

17
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:29,636
Yes.

18
00:04:30,136 --> 00:04:31,371
You're already flying out

19
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:32,672
at least twice a week.

20
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:34,607
And you still want to add more?

21
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:37,343
I've checked the schedule.

22
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:39,012
I can fit them in.

23
00:04:40,546 --> 00:04:41,314
Like you said,

24
00:04:42,548 --> 00:04:43,449
the purpose of traveling surgery

25
00:04:43,983 --> 00:04:44,484
is to let patients

26
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:45,585
who can't come to big cities

27
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:46,552
for treatment

28
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:47,787
receive timely care.

29
00:04:48,488 --> 00:04:49,622
Since I have the time

30
00:04:50,056 --> 00:04:50,823
and the ability,

31
00:04:51,157 --> 00:04:51,691
I hope I can

32
00:04:51,691 --> 00:04:52,558
do more surgeries

33
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:53,893
and save more people.

34
00:04:54,761 --> 00:04:56,496
I'm worried your body can't take it.

35
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:58,765
My health is fine.

36
00:04:59,132 --> 00:04:59,799
And don't worry.

37
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:00,733
I'll also arrange

38
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:01,668
all my work here properly.

39
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:03,069
Then...

40
00:05:03,403 --> 00:05:03,803
what do you think

41
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:04,103
about the hospital's

42
00:05:04,103 --> 00:05:04,837
TAVR cases?

43
00:05:05,371 --> 00:05:06,105
I heard

44
00:05:06,239 --> 00:05:07,073
you argued with Director Zhou

45
00:05:07,106 --> 00:05:07,874
yesterday.

46
00:05:09,075 --> 00:05:09,942
What I think doesn't matter.

47
00:05:12,211 --> 00:05:12,945
As long as you directors

48
00:05:12,945 --> 00:05:13,746
reach an agreement.

49
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:17,750
All right.

50
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:19,252
I'll arrange it.

51
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:20,319
Thank you, Director.

52
00:05:32,632 --> 00:05:33,333
Director Lin.

53
00:05:34,801 --> 00:05:35,668
The hybrid operating room

54
00:05:35,735 --> 00:05:36,235
was originally ours

55
00:05:36,269 --> 00:05:37,637
for the whole afternoon.

56
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:38,705
He finished his morning case,

57
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:39,505
then said he wanted to add another.

58
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:40,840
Fine. One more was acceptable.

59
00:05:41,307 --> 00:05:42,175
For your sake

60
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:42,608
and Dr. Fang's,

61
00:05:42,642 --> 00:05:43,276
I agreed to wait.

62
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:44,477
But just now,

63
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,745
the operating-room nurse

64
00:05:45,812 --> 00:05:47,013
told me he added yet another case.

65
00:05:49,315 --> 00:05:50,149
Elective or emergency?

66
00:05:50,283 --> 00:05:51,184
Elective.

67
00:05:51,551 --> 00:05:52,285
This patient

68
00:05:52,318 --> 00:05:53,252
came to my clinic two days ago.

69
00:05:53,453 --> 00:05:54,120
I recommended

70
00:05:54,153 --> 00:05:54,554
TAVR.

71
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:55,688
But according to our schedule,

72
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:56,756
it would have been two or three days later.

73
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,358
He said he'd think about it.

74
00:05:58,524 --> 00:05:58,891
Then,

75
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:00,159
he went straight to Cardiac Surgery,

76
00:06:00,326 --> 00:06:01,294
and they immediately let him jump the queue

77
00:06:01,327 --> 00:06:02,095
and arranged urgent surgery.

78
00:06:02,328 --> 00:06:02,729
It's absurd.

79
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:03,930
They're stealing both patients and operating-room time.

80
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:04,330
This is...

81
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:06,933
Wait.

82
00:06:13,906 --> 00:06:14,273
Director Zhou.

83
00:06:15,575 --> 00:06:16,042
Lin Yi.

84
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:17,143
Come outside.

85
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:23,850
We're almost ready for surgery.

86
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:25,051
Let's talk afterward.

87
00:06:26,152 --> 00:06:26,719
Come out with me.

88
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,467
What's going on?

89
00:06:43,669 --> 00:06:44,237
This afternoon,

90
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:45,304
the hybrid operating room

91
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:46,072
belongs to Cardiology.

92
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:47,774
Do you know what time it is?

93
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:48,841
I do.

94
00:06:49,942 --> 00:06:51,043
Then please leave.

95
00:06:51,844 --> 00:06:52,712
The patient inside

96
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:53,546
is critically ill

97
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:55,415
and needs surgery immediately.

98
00:06:55,748 --> 00:06:56,649
I've reviewed the chart.

99
00:06:57,016 --> 00:06:57,784
He's not that critical.

100
00:06:58,518 --> 00:06:59,752
And this is an elective case,

101
00:06:59,852 --> 00:07:00,753
not an emergency.

102
00:07:00,953 --> 00:07:01,854
That's your judgment,

103
00:07:02,488 --> 00:07:03,089
not mine.

104
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:04,223
Your judgment doesn't matter.

105
00:07:04,624 --> 00:07:05,625
Follow the rules.

106
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:06,392
Don't cut the line.

107
00:07:09,862 --> 00:07:10,730
Should we start anesthesia?

108
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:12,465
Not yet. Hold off.

109
00:07:12,865 --> 00:07:13,966
Why are you two doing this?

110
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:15,635
Now it's turned into this mess.

111
00:07:17,003 --> 00:07:17,403
I...

112
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:18,304
What do you mean, "I"?

113
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:19,772
This is my operating time.

114
00:07:22,074 --> 00:07:22,809
The operating-room schedule

115
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,010
was decided by hospital leadership.

116
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,011
It has nothing to do with me.

117
00:07:26,012 --> 00:07:27,013
You're not my superior.

118
00:07:27,346 --> 00:07:28,214
I don't have to listen to you.

119
00:07:28,714 --> 00:07:29,816
I'm the head of Cardiology.

120
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:32,051
This is my time.

121
00:07:32,251 --> 00:07:33,052
I decide.

122
00:07:33,753 --> 00:07:34,720
So you mean

123
00:07:34,787 --> 00:07:35,888
you want the patient taken off the table?

124
00:07:36,489 --> 00:07:38,124
That's your problem to solve.

125
00:07:50,636 --> 00:07:51,604
The surgery is canceled.

126
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:56,108
Director Zhou Xiaofeng won't allow it.

127
00:07:59,679 --> 00:08:00,046
Liu Dong.

128
00:08:00,746 --> 00:08:01,681
Arrange to take the patient down.

129
00:08:04,383 --> 00:08:05,318
Sir, I'm sorry.

130
00:08:05,451 --> 00:08:06,719
We may have to reschedule your surgery.

131
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:08,287
Yes, it's a last-minute notice.

132
00:08:08,287 --> 00:08:09,322
We'll make another arrangement.

133
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,601
This is ridiculous.

134
00:08:21,634 --> 00:08:23,069
Absolutely absurd.

135
00:08:23,302 --> 00:08:24,604
I've never heard of

136
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:25,671
a patient being put on the operating table

137
00:08:25,805 --> 00:08:26,873
and then sent away.

138
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:29,008
This is a top-tier hospital,

139
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:30,743
supposedly the best,

140
00:08:31,143 --> 00:08:31,744
yet you're acting like

141
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,079
an amateur troupe.

142
00:08:34,614 --> 00:08:35,848
We're truly sorry.

143
00:08:36,148 --> 00:08:37,517
There was a minor conflict in the process.

144
00:08:38,651 --> 00:08:39,452
Big hospitals

145
00:08:40,253 --> 00:08:41,320
always have limited resources.

146
00:08:41,754 --> 00:08:43,489
This isn't about limited resources.

147
00:08:43,756 --> 00:08:45,191
Your process is chaotic.

148
00:08:45,391 --> 00:08:47,493
You're treating patients' lives like a joke.

149
00:08:49,595 --> 00:08:50,162
I promise

150
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:52,665
we can operate tomorrow.

151
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,166
I'll arrange priority scheduling.

152
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:55,268
Tomorrow?

153
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:56,435
Forget it.

154
00:08:57,069 --> 00:08:57,637
I don't dare

155
00:08:57,637 --> 00:08:58,571
have surgery here anymore.

156
00:08:58,905 --> 00:08:59,672
Let's get discharged.

157
00:09:00,506 --> 00:09:01,707
You hear me? We're leaving.

158
00:09:04,911 --> 00:09:06,045
Brother, don't worry.

159
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:07,513
I'll take you to another hospital.

160
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,714
This place...

161
00:09:09,282 --> 00:09:09,782
Forget it.

162
00:09:10,549 --> 00:09:11,484
Brother, don't worry.

163
00:09:11,851 --> 00:09:12,852
I'll find you the best hospital.

164
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:14,320
Let's go.

165
00:09:14,787 --> 00:09:15,187
Don't worry.

166
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:23,729
Director Sheng, we need your signature.

167
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:28,067
Professor Fang.

168
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:29,869
The patient in Bed 11

169
00:09:30,002 --> 00:09:31,103
has had very little urine today

170
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,104
and a slight fever.

171
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:33,472
Could you come take a look?

172
00:09:33,706 --> 00:09:34,573
I'll go now.

173
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:35,841
Okay. Did you request a consult?

174
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:39,545
Dr. Fang is from Cardiac Surgery.

175
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:42,048
If you want her to manage a patient,

176
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,683
follow the consultation process.

177
00:09:46,285 --> 00:09:47,186
Starting tomorrow,

178
00:09:47,887 --> 00:09:48,587
all procedures

179
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:49,989
must be standardized again.

180
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:51,524
Especially cross-department work.

181
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:52,992
It can't stay as casual as before.

182
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,131
Director Sheng,

183
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:01,133
the comprehensive ICU

184
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:01,834
is meant to be comprehensive.

185
00:10:01,834 --> 00:10:02,635
The ICU

186
00:10:02,868 --> 00:10:03,836
is one of the core units

187
00:10:03,903 --> 00:10:05,037
of the Heart Center.

188
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,372
And my position

189
00:10:06,505 --> 00:10:08,007
was designed to cover

190
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:08,608
the overlapping ICU work

191
00:10:08,641 --> 00:10:09,442
of both departments.

192
00:10:09,508 --> 00:10:10,676
Your official post is in Cardiac Surgery.

193
00:10:11,210 --> 00:10:11,911
Is your workload

194
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:12,912
really that light?

195
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:14,914
I can handle it.

196
00:10:15,014 --> 00:10:16,048
It's all part of my job.

197
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:18,250
What about the patient in Bed 7?

198
00:10:18,317 --> 00:10:19,085
I have time tonight.

199
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:19,852
I can add the surgery.

200
00:10:19,986 --> 00:10:20,519
The patient left.

201
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:22,254
Left?

202
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:23,623
Where did he go?

203
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:24,991
Come with me.

204
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:30,429
Go on.

205
00:10:31,864 --> 00:10:32,965
Sisi, let's go.

206
00:10:35,668 --> 00:10:36,969
How could you argue

207
00:10:37,036 --> 00:10:37,870
in front of the patient?

208
00:10:38,504 --> 00:10:39,839
We didn't argue in front of him.

209
00:10:40,873 --> 00:10:42,174
I had everything ready

210
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:43,075
and was just waiting for anesthesia.

211
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:44,477
Then he suddenly came over

212
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:45,311
and said we couldn't operate.

213
00:10:45,444 --> 00:10:46,145
What could I do?

214
00:10:47,113 --> 00:10:48,047
I had an unexpected meeting.

215
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:48,948
I'd already spoken

216
00:10:49,048 --> 00:10:50,783
with the cath-lab head nurse.

217
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:52,284
After the meeting,

218
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:53,719
I planned to tell Director Zhou.

219
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:55,454
I should have called him first.

220
00:10:55,454 --> 00:10:56,322
It's my fault.

221
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:57,690
How could it be your fault?

222
00:10:58,290 --> 00:10:59,291
This was his problem.

223
00:10:59,291 --> 00:11:00,226
Your skills are so good

224
00:11:01,093 --> 00:11:02,094
that patients are being diverted to you.

225
00:11:02,228 --> 00:11:03,362
Cardiology naturally has objections.

226
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:05,464
That's understandable.

227
00:11:05,965 --> 00:11:06,799
Director,

228
00:11:09,802 --> 00:11:10,169
about that patient,

229
00:11:10,436 --> 00:11:12,071
should I try

230
00:11:12,238 --> 00:11:13,239
to get him back for surgery?

231
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:14,440
We've said everything we could.

232
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:16,742
The patient has already lost

233
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:18,077
his sense of safety and trust.

234
00:11:18,110 --> 00:11:19,078
We can't force it.

235
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:20,212
But I've been treating him all along.

236
00:11:22,948 --> 00:11:24,350
So...

237
00:11:24,583 --> 00:11:24,984
I should be the one

238
00:11:25,584 --> 00:11:26,986
to do the surgery.

239
00:11:27,753 --> 00:11:28,587
Let him go.

240
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:30,156
Another hospital can treat him too.

241
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:32,358
Anyway,

242
00:11:33,092 --> 00:11:33,926
after this fight,

243
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:35,561
Cardiac Surgery, Cardiology,

244
00:11:35,828 --> 00:11:36,495
and the patient—

245
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,564
none of the three sides won.

246
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:42,568
Okay.

247
00:11:42,568 --> 00:11:43,335
I'm heading over now.

248
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:12,965
Since returning from Europe,

249
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:13,866
he's become a different person.

250
00:12:15,534 --> 00:12:16,268
I don't have

251
00:12:16,268 --> 00:12:17,670
extra energy to keep accommodating him.

252
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,638
The "strike team" sign is gone.

253
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:21,240
We made everything clear.

254
00:12:21,474 --> 00:12:22,842
Yet he still insists on doing things his way.

255
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:26,412
Cardiology's patients are patients too.

256
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:28,147
If I keep yielding,

257
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:29,682
the patients will suffer.

258
00:12:30,683 --> 00:12:31,383
And everyone

259
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:32,585
in the department has strong objections to him.

260
00:12:32,985 --> 00:12:34,286
I can only state my position publicly.

261
00:12:35,187 --> 00:12:36,122
He keeps occupying

262
00:12:36,122 --> 00:12:36,922
the hybrid operating room.

263
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:37,923
That's definitely wrong.

264
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:39,625
I warned him too.

265
00:12:40,392 --> 00:12:42,094
He said Director Sheng would coordinate,

266
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:44,463
but Director Sheng never

267
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:45,598
communicated with you, right?

268
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:47,366
Why would he communicate with me?

269
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:50,436
I've noticed it too.

270
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,104
It seems like he's deliberately

271
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:53,639
trying to split Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery apart.

272
00:12:54,473 --> 00:12:55,774
Just now in the ICU,

273
00:12:55,808 --> 00:12:57,476
he said the consultation process

274
00:12:58,410 --> 00:12:59,411
should be restarted.

275
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:00,045
But doesn't that go against

276
00:13:00,079 --> 00:13:00,913
the original purpose of the comprehensive ICU?

277
00:13:04,383 --> 00:13:05,484
He has a problem with me

278
00:13:05,751 --> 00:13:06,986
and is using this as an excuse.

279
00:13:09,321 --> 00:13:10,489
If he dares give you trouble,

280
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:12,024
you have to tell me.

281
00:13:14,593 --> 00:13:15,961
When Director Sheng took it out on you,

282
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:17,963
Lin Yi wasn't there, right?

283
00:13:18,597 --> 00:13:19,331
He wasn't.

284
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:21,934
If Lin Yi had been there,

285
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:23,469
he probably wouldn't have

286
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:24,236
acted that way.

287
00:13:24,904 --> 00:13:26,172
So you didn't tell Lin Yi either.

288
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:29,475
In his current state,

289
00:13:33,245 --> 00:13:34,680
I can handle my own problems.

290
00:13:35,014 --> 00:13:35,648
Don't worry.

291
00:13:39,718 --> 00:13:40,486
What about you two?

292
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:42,254
How have things been lately?

293
00:13:43,455 --> 00:13:44,523
You noticed too.

294
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:46,592
Since coming back,

295
00:13:47,393 --> 00:13:48,494
he's been acting

